                        <script type="text/template">
                            ##Background
                        </script>
                    </section>
                    <section data-background-image='images/thailand/jungle5.jpg'>
                        Degradation effects as much as 10x amount of forests as deforestation (IPCC 4th Assessment Report)
                    </section>
                    <section data-markdown data-background-image='images/thailand/jungle5.jpg'>
                        <script type="text/template">
                            ### Terrestrial carbon sink is still a source of large uncertainty.
                            * How much carbon is being stored in forest biomass?
                            * To what extent is that biomass changing? 
                            * How will it respond to climate change?
                        </script>
                     </section>
                    <section data-markdown data-background-image='images/thailand/jungle5.jpg'>
                        <script type="text/template">
                            REDD+: Reduced Emissions From Deforestation and *Degradation*
                        </script>
                     </section>
                    <section data-background-image='images/thailand/jungle5.jpg'>
                        Currently no operational way of detecting degradation
                     </section>
                     <section data-background-image='images/thailand/jungle5.jpg'>
                        Difficulties due to highly varying causes and subtle impact on canopy
                      </section>
                </section>
                <section>
                    <section data-markdown data-background-image='images/thailand/jungle4.jpg'>
                        <script type="text/template">
                            ##Objectives
                        </script>
                    </section>
                    <section data-markdown data-background-image='images/thailand/jungle4.jpg'>
                        <script type="text/template">
                            <p style="text-align: left; font-size: 64px;">Technical Objective</p>
                            * Develop a methodology to automatically detect and quantify subtle changes in biomass

                            <br>
                            <p style="text-align: left; font-size: 64px;">Research Objective</p>
                            * Reduce uncertainty in estimates of carbon emissions from forest degradation
                        </script>
                    </section>
                    <section data-background-image='images/thailand/jungle4.jpg'>
                        1. Evaluate the responses in both optical and radar time series to varying forms of forest degradation.
                    </section>
                    <section data-background-image='images/thailand/jungle4.jpg'>
                        2. Develop a methodology to identify areas of forest that have been degraded over time.
                     </section>
                     <section data-background-image='images/thailand/jungle4.jpg'>
                        3. Map degraded forests across Thailand 
                      </section>
                     <section data-background-image='images/thailand/jungle4.jpg'>
                        4. Investigate the relationship between the temporal responses of degradation in remote sensing data and biomass reduction at the plot level.
                      </section>
                     <section data-background-image='images/thailand/jungle4.jpg'>
                        5. Calculate the carbon emissions from degradation for Thailand and compare it to estimates of emissions from deforestation.
                      </section>
                </section>
                <section>
